===Etymology===
Anastasius is a male given name which comes from Koine Greek. It means "resurrection". The name, and its more common female counterpart, [[Anastasia]] were originally given to children who were born around Eastertime during the early years of Christianity.

The names "Anastasi" (also spelled "Anastazi"), "Tas", "Taz" "Stas" and "Staz" are derived from Anastasius.

